message.content: Yes, there are infinitely many even numbers. The sequence of even numbers is given by \(2, 4, 6, 8, 10, \ldots\), which can be expressed mathematically as the set \(\{2n \mid n \in \mathbb{N}\}\), where \(\mathbb{N}\) denotes the set of natural numbers. Since \(\mathbb{N}\) is infinite, the set of even numbers is also infinite.
Yes, there are infinitely many even numbers. An even number is of the form \(2k\) where \(k\) is an integer. Since there are infinitely many integers \(k\), there are infinitely many even numbers.

Yes, there are infinitely many even numbers. Formally, the set of even numbers can be expressed as \(\{ 2n \mid n \in \mathbb{Z} \}\). Since the integers \(\mathbb{Z}\) are infinite, the set of even numbers is also infinite.
